p://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=4009&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /><div><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2010/05/01/stephan-spencer-seo-wordpress-sf10/"><img alt="Stephan Spencer: SEO for WordPress" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/fPL4192U/stephan-spencer_std.original.jpg" width="160" height="120" /></a></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 24 Jun 2010 20:30:10 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:11:"Ryan Markel";}s:7:"summary";s:1383:"<div id="x-video-5" class="video-player">\n\n</div>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/4009/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=4009&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /><div><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2010/05/01/stephan-spencer-seo-wordpress-sf10/"><img alt="Stephan Spencer: SEO for WordPress" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/fPL4192U/stephan-spencer_std.original.jpg" width="160" height="120" /></a></div>";}i:2;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:23:"Matt: Million in a Week";s:4:"guid";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=35028";s:4:"link";s:39:"http://ma.tt/2010/06/million-in-a-week/";s:11:"description";s:309:"<p>WordPress 3.0, <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2010/06/thelonious/">released last Thursday</a>, has already <a href="http://wordpress.org/download/counter/">passed one million downloads</a>. <img src="http://ma.tt/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 24 Jun 2010 14:41:20 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:309:"<p>WordPress 3.0, <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2010/06/thelonious/">released last Thursday</a>, has already <a href="http://wordpress.org/download/counter/">passed one million downloads</a>. <img src="http://ma.tt/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>";}i:3;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:20:"Matt: Montreal Quake";s:4:"guid";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=35024";s:4:"link";s:36:"http://ma.tt/2010/06/montreal-quake/";s:11:"description";s:246:"<p>I never expected I would leave San Francisco and <a href="http://news.blogs.cnn.com/2010/06/23/usgs-5-5-magnitude-earthuake-strikes-canada/">experience a quake in Montreal</a>. It was pretty slight here, but I definitely noticed something.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 18:47:08 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:246:"<p>I never expected I would leave San Francisco and <a href="http://news.blogs.cnn.com/2010/06/23/usgs-5-5-magnitude-earthuake-strikes-canada/">experience a quake in Montreal</a>. It was pretty slight here, but I definitely noticed something.</p>";}i:4;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:26:"Joseph: WordCamp Utah 2010";s:4:"guid";s:30:"http://josephscott.org/?p=2441";s:4:"link";s:59:"http://josephscott.org/archives/2010/06/wordcamp-utah-2010/";s:11:"description";s:1542:"<p>It&#8217;s been nearly two years since the first WordCamp Utah, a packed house at the Novell campus in Provo.  Now plans are in place for a WordCamp Utah 2010!</p>\n<p>August 28th is the day, University of Utah is the place.  There will be updates at <a href="http://2010.utah.wordcamp.org/">http://2010.utah.wordcamp.org/</a> as more of the details get filled in.  I can say we are planning for two tracks, with one focused more on developer topics.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in speaking send us a presentation proposal via the <a href="http://2010.utah.wordcamp.org/contact/">contact form</a> on the 2010 site.  We&#8217;re also looking for sponsors and volunteers (especially if you can help record video of each session).</p>\n<p>Mark Saturday, August 28th on your calendar, come spend the day with the Utah WordPress community.  Spread the word, use the #wcut hash tag for WordCamp Utah.</p>\n\n\n<p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href="http://josephscott.org/archives/2010/04/wordcamp-san-francisco-2010/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordCamp San Francisco &#8211; 2010">WordCamp San Francisco &#8211; 2010</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://josephscott.org/archives/2010/06/wordcamp-sf-2010-presentation-video/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordCamp SF 2010 Presentation Video">WordCamp SF 2010 Presentation Video</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://josephscott.org/archives/2009/02/ill-be-at-wordcamp-denver/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: I&#8217;ll Be At WordCamp Denver">I&#8217;ll Be At WordCamp Denver</a></li>\n</ol></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 16:05:12 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:12:"Joseph Scott";}s:7:"summary";s:1542:"<p>It&#8217;s been nearly two years since the first WordCamp Utah, a packed house at the Novell campus in Provo.  Now plans are in place for a WordCamp Utah 2010!</p>\n<p>August 28th is the day, University of Utah is the place.  There will be updates at <a href="http://2010.utah.wordcamp.org/">http://2010.utah.wordcamp.org/</a> as more of the details get filled in.  I can say we are planning for two tracks, with one focused more on developer topics.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in speaking send us a presentation proposal via the <a href="http://2010.utah.wordcamp.org/contact/">contact form</a> on the 2010 site.  We&#8217;re also looking for sponsors and volunteers (especially if you can help record video of each session).</p>\n<p>Mark Saturday, August 28th on your calendar, come spend the day with the Utah WordPress community.  Spread the word, use the #wcut hash tag for WordCamp Utah.</p>\n\n\n<p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href="http://josephscott.org/archives/2010/04/wordcamp-san-francisco-2010/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordCamp San Francisco &#8211; 2010">WordCamp San Francisco &#8211; 2010</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://josephscott.org/archives/2010/06/wordcamp-sf-2010-presentation-video/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordCamp SF 2010 Presentation Video">WordCamp SF 2010 Presentation Video</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://josephscott.org/archives/2009/02/ill-be-at-wordcamp-denver/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: I&#8217;ll Be At WordCamp Denver">I&#8217;ll Be At WordCamp Denver</a></li>\n</ol></p>";}i:5;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:50:"Alex King: Crowd Favorite is Hiring: Sr. Developer";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://alexking.org/?p=4444";s:4:"link";s:73:"http://alexking.org/blog/2010/06/23/crowd-favorite-is-hiring-sr-developer";s:11:"description";s:2011:"<p>I&#8217;m looking for a sharp web developer to join my team in our Denver office at <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com">Crowd Favorite</a>. I want to find someone with a relatively, broad range of experience and skills &#8211; if you&#8217;ve been building cool stuff for the last few years, you&#8217;ve probably got it. We are looking for the right technical, cultural and geographic fit for our team.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll get to work on a bunch of interesting and diverse projects. Some of our recent projects have included:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Advanced WordPress websites, plugins, themes, integrations and products. We build a <em>lot</em> of stuff with WordPress.</li>\n<li>A site migration tool for importing legacy websites into WordPress multi-site (complete with testing routines).</li>\n<li>Facebook integration and platform development.</li>\n<li>A web service for processing gobs of data running on Amazon&#8217;s cloud. The system is comprised of 10 different individual components, all talking to each other&#8217;s web services.</li>\n<li>Customizable financial dashboards (web application).</li>\n<li>An integration into numerous web services to power a custom web application that provides a different kind of productized web analytics.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We have a casual, collaborative team environment. You can choose your OS and development tools (all of our systems are cross-platform or web based) and get to have a say in development approaches, policies, best practices, etc.</p>\n<p>If these kinds of things sound interesting to you, <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com/jobs/">we&#8217;d like to hear from you</a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>We also have two internship positions (developer and designer/front-end developer) available &#8211; if you want to learn about building with WordPress, Open Source, web standards and modern best practices, we can give you some great experience building things people actually use.</p>\n<img src="http://alexking.org/wp/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=4444&type=feed" alt="" />";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 15:10:46 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Alex";}s:7:"summary";s:2011:"<p>I&#8217;m looking for a sharp web developer to join my team in our Denver office at <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com">Crowd Favorite</a>. I want to find someone with a relatively, broad range of experience and skills &#8211; if you&#8217;ve been building cool stuff for the last few years, you&#8217;ve probably got it. We are looking for the right technical, cultural and geographic fit for our team.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll get to work on a bunch of interesting and diverse projects. Some of our recent projects have included:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Advanced WordPress websites, plugins, themes, integrations and products. We build a <em>lot</em> of stuff with WordPress.</li>\n<li>A site migration tool for importing legacy websites into WordPress multi-site (complete with testing routines).</li>\n<li>Facebook integration and platform development.</li>\n<li>A web service for processing gobs of data running on Amazon&#8217;s cloud. The system is comprised of 10 different individual components, all talking to each other&#8217;s web services.</li>\n<li>Customizable financial dashboards (web application).</li>\n<li>An integration into numerous web services to power a custom web application that provides a different kind of productized web analytics.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We have a casual, collaborative team environment. You can choose your OS and development tools (all of our systems are cross-platform or web based) and get to have a say in development approaches, policies, best practices, etc.</p>\n<p>If these kinds of things sound interesting to you, <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com/jobs/">we&#8217;d like to hear from you</a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>We also have two internship positions (developer and designer/front-end developer) available &#8211; if you want to learn about building with WordPress, Open Source, web standards and modern best practices, we can give you some great experience building things people actually use.</p>\n<img src="http://alexking.org/wp/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=4444&type=feed" alt="" />";}i:6;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:37:"Alex King: WordPress 3.0 Upgrade Help";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://alexking.org/?p=4456";s:4:"link";s:62:"http://alexking.org/blog/2010/06/23/wordpress-3-0-upgrade-help";s:11:"description";s:786:"<p>I&#8217;ve been keeping an eye on what folks are saying about their WordPress 3.0 upgrade experiences and it appears that most folks are finding the upgrade to be a pretty smooth sailing experience. Kudos to <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2010/06/thelonious/" rel="external">everyone who contributed to 3.0</a>, this is not a small accomplishment (especially considering the fundamental changes in 3.0).</p>\n<p>If you do need any help upgrading to WordPress 3.0, don&#8217;t hesitate to contact my <a href="http://wphelpcenter.com">WordPress HelpCenter</a> team. You can call them directly at: (303) 395-1346 from 9am-8pm US/Eastern M-F or email anytime to help@wphelpcenter.com.</p>\n<img src="http://alexking.org/wp/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=4456&type=feed" alt="" />";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 15:06:11 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Alex";}s:7:"summary";s:786:"<p>I&#8217;ve been keeping an eye on what folks are saying about their WordPress 3.0 upgrade experiences and it appears that most folks are finding the upgrade to be a pretty smooth sailing experience. Kudos to <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2010/06/thelonious/" rel="external">everyone who contributed to 3.0</a>, this is not a small accomplishment (especially considering the fundamental changes in 3.0).</p>\n<p>If you do need any help upgrading to WordPress 3.0, don&#8217;t hesitate to contact my <a href="http://wphelpcenter.com">WordPress HelpCenter</a> team. You can call them directly at: (303) 395-1346 from 9am-8pm US/Eastern M-F or email anytime to help@wphelpcenter.com.</p>\n<img src="http://alexking.org/wp/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=4456&type=feed" alt="" />";}i:7;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:56:"WordPress Podcast: Digging into CSS Trickery & WordPress";s:4:"guid";s:30:"http://wp-community.org/?p=604";s:4:"link";s:63:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wordpresspodcast/~3/kJAeSfNwd5w/";s:11:"description";s:870:"<p>Today Joost is joined by Chris Coyier, one of the authors of <a href="http://digwp.com/">Digging into WordPress</a> and the founder of <a href="http://css-tricks.com/">CSS Tricks</a>. Chris and Joost talk about a lot of different subjects, ranging from their individual history with CSS sites to what Chris dubbed &#8220;the big three&#8221; updates in WordPress 3.0 (custom post types, menus, multi site) and to how Chris designs a site.</p>\n<h2>Plugin picks of the week</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Joost picked one of his own, <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/minimum-comment-length/">Minimum Comment Length</a></li>\n<li>Which inspired Chris to pick another comments related plugin: <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/feature-comments/">Feature comments</a></li>\n</ul>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wordpresspodcast/~4/kJAeSfNwd5w" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 10:11:40 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:54:"joost@pressthis.com (Joost de Valk & Frederick Townes)";}s:7:"summary";s:870:"<p>Today Joost is joined by Chris Coyier, one of the authors of <a href="http://digwp.com/">Digging into WordPress</a> and the founder of <a href="http://css-tricks.com/">CSS Tricks</a>. Chris and Joost talk about a lot of different subjects, ranging from their individual history with CSS sites to what Chris dubbed &#8220;the big three&#8221; updates in WordPress 3.0 (custom post types, menus, multi site) and to how Chris designs a site.</p>\n<h2>Plugin picks of the week</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Joost picked one of his own, <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/minimum-comment-length/">Minimum Comment Length</a></li>\n<li>Which inspired Chris to pick another comments related plugin: <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/feature-comments/">Feature comments</a></li>\n</ul>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wordpresspodcast/~4/kJAeSfNwd5w" height="1" width="1" />";}i:8;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:43:"Donncha: WordPress 3.0 Domain Mapping 0.5.2";s:4:"guid";s:29:"http://ocaoimh.ie/?p=89495930";s:4:"link";s:50:"http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-30-domain-mapping-052/";s:11:"description";s:2048:"<p>I&#8217;ve just released <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping/">WordPress Domain Mapping 0.5.2</a>. This plugin allows you to map any domain on to your WordPress 3.0 or WordPress MU website.</p>\n<p>New in this release:\n<ul>\n<li> WordPress 3.0 support.</li>\n<li> Added &#8220;domains&#8221; page for superadmin to add domains to any blog. The user&#8217;s domains page can be disabled by the superadmin too.</li>\n<li> Added support for &#8220;www.&#8221; prefix in front of domains.</li>\n<li> Allow dashboard to redirect to mapped or original domain.</li>\n<li> Better support for SSL</li>\n<li> Translation file added for localization.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For security reasons remote login is now disabled if the dashboard is redirected to the mapped domain. There is a tiny chance of a man-in-the-middle attack during redirection, but it&#8217;s just as likely to happen when you&#8217;re logging in and sending your username/password to the login form. Call me paranoid.</p>\n<p>I would like to thank <a href="http://wpmututorials.com/">Ron and Andrea</a> who were a huge help developing and testing this release. Andrea has written a great post on <a href="http://wpmututorials.com/basics/everything-you-wanted-to-know-about-creating-a-network-of-multiple-sites-in-3-0/">creating a network in WordPress 3.0</a> plus <a href="http://wpmututorials.com/how-to/upgrading-from-wpmu-to-wp-3-0/">instructions on upgrading from WordPress MU</a>. Great stuff!</p>\n<p><strong>Related Posts</strong><ul><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress MU Domain Mapping">WordPress MU Domain Mapping</a></li><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping-01/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.1">WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.1</a></li><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping-05/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.5">WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.5</a></li></ul></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 09:53:43 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Donncha";}s:7:"summary";s:2048:"<p>I&#8217;ve just released <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping/">WordPress Domain Mapping 0.5.2</a>. This plugin allows you to map any domain on to your WordPress 3.0 or WordPress MU website.</p>\n<p>New in this release:\n<ul>\n<li> WordPress 3.0 support.</li>\n<li> Added &#8220;domains&#8221; page for superadmin to add domains to any blog. The user&#8217;s domains page can be disabled by the superadmin too.</li>\n<li> Added support for &#8220;www.&#8221; prefix in front of domains.</li>\n<li> Allow dashboard to redirect to mapped or original domain.</li>\n<li> Better support for SSL</li>\n<li> Translation file added for localization.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For security reasons remote login is now disabled if the dashboard is redirected to the mapped domain. There is a tiny chance of a man-in-the-middle attack during redirection, but it&#8217;s just as likely to happen when you&#8217;re logging in and sending your username/password to the login form. Call me paranoid.</p>\n<p>I would like to thank <a href="http://wpmututorials.com/">Ron and Andrea</a> who were a huge help developing and testing this release. Andrea has written a great post on <a href="http://wpmututorials.com/basics/everything-you-wanted-to-know-about-creating-a-network-of-multiple-sites-in-3-0/">creating a network in WordPress 3.0</a> plus <a href="http://wpmututorials.com/how-to/upgrading-from-wpmu-to-wp-3-0/">instructions on upgrading from WordPress MU</a>. Great stuff!</p>\n<p><strong>Related Posts</strong><ul><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress MU Domain Mapping">WordPress MU Domain Mapping</a></li><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping-01/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.1">WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.1</a></li><li><a href="http://ocaoimh.ie/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping-05/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.5">WordPress MU Domain Mapping 0.5</a></li></ul></p>";}i:9;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:59:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 06/22";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=8213";s:4:"link";s:87:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2010/06/22/wordpress-theme-releases-for-0622/";s:11:"description";s:2416:"<h4><a href="http://webhostinghelpguy.inmotionhosting.com/wordpress/twenty-ten-inverted-wordpress-theme/">Twenty Ten Inverted</a></h4>\n<p><a rel="thumbnail" href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TopTenInverted.jpg"><img title="Top Ten Inverted" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TopTenInverted_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="Top Ten Inverted" width="244" height="141" /></a></p>\n<p>2 column theme for WordPress 3.0 which has inverted colours of Top Ten</p>\n<h4><a href="http://www.blogging-inside.de/wordpress-themes/twenty-ten-wordpress-3-0-theme-blogging-inside-edition/">Twenty Ten Blogging Inside Edition</a></h4>\n<p><a rel="thumbnail" href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TwentyTenBlogginEdition.jpg"><img title="TwentyTenBlogginEdition" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TwentyTenBlogginEdition_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="TwentyTenBlogginEdition" width="244" height="203" /></a></p>\n<p>Twenty Ten Blogging Inside Edition WordPress 3.0 Theme is based on the new WordPress 3.0 default Theme with a few modifications.</p>\n<p>The Sidebar is optimized for Adsense 236px Ads. Changed sidebar with a different look&amp;feel and with posts metadata grey frame to make the posts more compact</p>\n<h4><a href="http://wp-skins.info/2010/06/21/free-wordpress-theme-simplytext.html">SimpleText</a></h4>\n<p><a rel="thumbnail" href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/SimpleText.jpg"><img title="SimpleText" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/SimpleText_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="SimpleText" width="244" height="152" /></a></p>\n<p>SimpleText &#8211; a simple theme for Wordpress, sidebar on the left, in the theme used not standard fonts (js typeface), theme compatible with wordpress 3.0, to create a paging navigation use the plugin wp-pagenavi.</p>\n<h4><a href="http://mainolo.com/blog/2010/06/goodness-free-wordpress-theme/">Goodness </a></h4>\n<p><a href="http://mainolo.com/goodness/"><img title="goodness" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/goodness.png" border="0" alt="goodness" width="224" height="168" /></a></p>\n<p>Goodness is a two-column layout WordPress theme, with a righthand sidebar with a horizontal dropdown jQuery custom menu, a replaceable logo area, custom header and paged- and threaded- comments.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 23 Jun 2010 01:00:29 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Perurry";}s:7:"summary";s:2416:"<h4><a href="http://webhostinghelpguy.inmotionhosting.com/wordpress/twenty-ten-inverted-wordpress-theme/">Twenty Ten Inverted</a></h4>\n<p><a rel="thumbnail" href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TopTenInverted.jpg"><img title="Top Ten Inverted" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TopTenInverted_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="Top Ten Inverted" width="244" height="141" /></a></p>\n<p>2 column theme for WordPress 3.0 which has inverted colours of Top Ten</p>\n<h4><a href="http://www.blogging-inside.de/wordpress-themes/twenty-ten-wordpress-3-0-theme-blogging-inside-edition/">Twenty Ten Blogging Inside Edition</a></h4>\n<p><a rel="thumbnail" href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TwentyTenBlogginEdition.jpg"><img title="TwentyTenBlogginEdition" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TwentyTenBlogginEdition_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="TwentyTenBlogginEdition" width="244" height="203" /></a></p>\n<p>Twenty Ten Blogging Inside Edition WordPress 3.0 Theme is based on the new WordPress 3.0 default Theme with a few modifications.</p>\n<p>The Sidebar is optimized for Adsense 236px Ads. Changed sidebar with a different look&amp;feel and with posts metadata grey frame to make the posts more compact</p>\n<h4><a href="http://wp-skins.info/2010/06/21/free-wordpress-theme-simplytext.html">SimpleText</a></h4>\n<p><a rel="thumbnail" href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/SimpleText.jpg"><img title="SimpleText" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/SimpleText_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="SimpleText" width="244" height="152" /></a></p>\n<p>SimpleText &#8211; a simple theme for Wordpress, sidebar on the left, in the theme used not standard fonts (js typeface), theme compatible with wordpress 3.0, to create a paging navigation use the plugin wp-pagenavi.</p>\n<h4><a href="http://mainolo.com/blog/2010/06/goodness-free-wordpress-theme/">Goodness </a></h4>\n<p><a href="http://mainolo.com/goodness/"><img title="goodness" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/goodness.png" border="0" alt="goodness" width="224" height="168" /></a></p>\n<p>Goodness is a two-column layout WordPress theme, with a righthand sidebar with a horizontal dropdown jQuery custom menu, a replaceable logo area, custom header and paged- and threaded- comments.</p>";}i:10;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:49:"WordPress.tv: Yoav Farhi: Right to Left WordPress";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=3999";s:4:"link";s:68:"http://wordpress.tv/2010/05/01/yoav-farhi-right-to-left-themes-sf10/";s:11:"description";s:1381:"<div id="x-video-6" class="video-player">\n\n</div>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=3999&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /><div><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2010/05/01/yoav-farhi-right-to-left-themes-sf10/"><img alt="Yoav Farhi: Right to Left WordPress" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/0J79rJbL/yoav-farhi_std.original.jpg" width="160" height="120" /></a></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 22 Jun 2010 21:15:10 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:11:"Ryan Markel";}s:7:"summary";s:1381:"<div id="x-video-6" class="video-player">\n\n</div>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/3999/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=3999&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /><div><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2010/05/01/yoav-farhi-right-to-left-themes-sf10/"><img alt="Yoav Farhi: Right to Left WordPress" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/0J79rJbL/yoav-farhi_std.original.jpg" width="160" height="120" /></a></div>";}i:11;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:32:"Gravatar: Profile Pages <3 hCard";s:4:"guid";s:31:"http://blog.gravatar.com/?p=218";s:4:"link";s:56:"http://blog.gravatar.com/2010/06/22/hcard-profile-pages/";s:11:"description";s:2805:"<p>Did you know that your profile pages are fully marked up using <a href="http://microformats.org/wiki/hcard">hCard</a>? hCard is a <a href="http://microformats.org/">microformat</a> for programmatically embedding information about people, companies, organizations, and places in HTML and other markup languages. The screenshot below describes some of the main markup involved on a profile page</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Email address</strong> marked up with <code>class=email</code> (only available via JS/client-side parsing due to spam-protection measures)</li>\n<li><strong>IM accounts</strong> marked up using <code>class=url</code> (some values only available via JS/client-side parsing due to spam-protection measures)</li>\n<li><strong>Phone numbers</strong> marked up with <code>class=tel</code> (using type/value subproperties)</li>\n<li><strong>Verified accounts</strong> marked up with <code>class=url</code> and <code>rel=me</code></li>\n<li><strong>Name</strong> marked up with <code>class=fn</code></li>\n<li><strong>Personal Links</strong> are marked up with <code>class=url</code></li>\n<li><strong>Image</strong> (main Gravatar) is marked up using <code>class=photo</code></li>\n</ol>\n<div id="attachment_219" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://gravatar.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/hcard-details.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-219" title="hcard-details" src="http://gravatar.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/hcard-details.png?w=700&#038;h=524" alt="hCard on Profile Pages" width="700" height="524" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">hCard on Profile Pages</p></div>\n<p>There&#8217;s more profile-data goodness coming soon, so check back here for the latest.</p>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=blog.gravatar.com&blog=1886259&post=218&subd=gravatar&ref=&feed=1" />";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 22 Jun 2010 20:26:41 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:11:"Beau Lebens";}s:7:"summary";s:2805:"<p>Did you know that your profile pages are fully marked up using <a href="http://microformats.org/wiki/hcard">hCard</a>? hCard is a <a href="http://microformats.org/">microformat</a> for programmatically embedding information about people, companies, organizations, and places in HTML and other markup languages. The screenshot below describes some of the main markup involved on a profile page</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Email address</strong> marked up with <code>class=email</code> (only available via JS/client-side parsing due to spam-protection measures)</li>\n<li><strong>IM accounts</strong> marked up using <code>class=url</code> (some values only available via JS/client-side parsing due to spam-protection measures)</li>\n<li><strong>Phone numbers</strong> marked up with <code>class=tel</code> (using type/value subproperties)</li>\n<li><strong>Verified accounts</strong> marked up with <code>class=url</code> and <code>rel=me</code></li>\n<li><strong>Name</strong> marked up with <code>class=fn</code></li>\n<li><strong>Personal Links</strong> are marked up with <code>class=url</code></li>\n<li><strong>Image</strong> (main Gravatar) is marked up using <code>class=photo</code></li>\n</ol>\n<div id="attachment_219" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://gravatar.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/hcard-details.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-219" title="hcard-details" src="http://gravatar.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/hcard-details.png?w=700&#038;h=524" alt="hCard on Profile Pages" width="700" height="524" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">hCard on Profile Pages</p></div>\n<p>There&#8217;s more profile-data goodness coming soon, so check back here for the latest.</p>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/gravatar.wordpress.com/218/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=blog.gravatar.com&blog=1886259&post=218&subd=gravatar&ref=&feed=1" />";}i:12;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:50:"WordPress.tv: Beau Lebens: Gravatar Open Profiles";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=3995";s:4:"link";s:66:"http://wordpress.tv/2010/05/01/beau-lebens-gravatar-profiles-sf10/";s:11:"description";s:1406:"<div id="x-video-7" class="video-player">\n\n</div>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/3995/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0